snippet: Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, the two mortgage finance giants, reported some of their best quarterly results since the real estate collapse.
abstract: Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, the two mortgage finance giants, report some of their best quarterly results since the real estate collapse; Fannie Mae posts second-quarter net income of $5.1 billion, compared with loss of $2.9 billion in year-ago quarter; Freddie Mac reports second-quarter profit of $3 billion, compared with loss of $2.1 billion in the year-ago quarter.
lead_paragraph: Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, the two mortgage finance giants, reported some of their best quarterly results since the real estate collapse.
